PHASE 3 — SPORTS-SPECIFIC LOGIC & FAILSAFES
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Goal: Implement all mechanics specific to live sports markets.

[ ] 3.1  3-Second In-Play Delay Handler
         — When order enters 3-second countdown, spawn a watchdog task
         — Watchdog polls GET /price at 100ms intervals
         — If implied probability shifts >1.5% → fire CancelOrder immediately
         — Use tokio::time::timeout to enforce hard deadline
[ ] 3.2  Pre-Game Order Wipe Listener
         — Subscribe to game-start events from sports data API
         — At game_start signal: cancel ALL open orders for that market_id
         — Flush local order cache
[ ] 3.3  Sports Market Discovery
         — Gamma API: GET /sports for available sports tags
         — GET /events?tag_id=X&active=true&closed=false for active markets
         — Filter for markets where RN1 has shown historical activity
[ ] 3.4  Volatility Filter
         — Track implied probability change rate (Δprice / Δtime) per market
         — Refuse to enter positions in markets with Δ > 5% in last 30 seconds
[ ] 3.5  Negative Risk (-Risk) market support
         — negRisk=true markets use different settlement logic
         — Implement separate tick size handling

Deliverables:  /src/sports_handler.rs, /src/failsafe.rs, /src/market_scanner.rs

